## Steps

### step 1
id: find-ask-altair-button
instruction: On any active work item card in the Work Queue, find and click the "Ask Altair" button.
success_criteria: The Altair AI panel has opened, pre-filled with context about that specific work item (title, description, linked record).
anchor: "Ask Altair"
on_success: next
on_stuck: Every active work item has an "Ask Altair" option — a button or link on the item card.

### step 2
id: wait-for-altair-response
instruction: Altair processes the work item context automatically. You'll see "Altair is on it..." briefly, then a response with analysis or suggested next steps.
success_criteria: Altair has responded with guidance specific to the work item.
anchor: "Altair response"
on_success: next
on_stuck: Wait a moment — Altair processes the context and responds automatically.

### step 3
id: ask-follow-up-questions
instruction: Ask follow-up questions in the chat to get deeper guidance. For example: "Why was this claim denied?", "Should I appeal or correct?", "Draft an appeal letter for this denial", "What's the filing deadline for this payer?"
success_criteria: You have the information you need to take action on the work item.
anchor: "chat input"
on_success: completion
on_stuck: Type in the chat box at the bottom of the Altair panel and press Enter.

## Completion Message
altair has given you guidance. take action on the work item using what you've learned, or keep the conversation going if you have more questions. your conversation history is saved so you can come back to it.

